 {"id":"ft-zoxxq","title":"[STRATEGIC/MEDIUM] crate::wezterm pseudo-boundary: 7748 LOC, 31 core importers, 48 vendored frankenterm/ subcrates — 'optional' claim is fiction","description":"Modes-of-reasoning F3: wezterm.rs defines WeztermHandle trait but also 7748 lines of concrete types (WeztermClient, PaneInfo, SpawnTarget, etc.) imported as crate::wezterm::* by 31 files. Plus wezterm_native.rs + 48 vendored frankenterm/<crate>/ directories. Removing wezterm would rewrite 40% of core. AGENTS.md calls it 'implementation boundary' — that framing is aspirational. Either (a) extract a true mux-backend trait with concrete type erasure, or (b) commit to the 'this IS a wezterm fork' identity and simplify.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-04-24T19:16:26.747900Z","created_by":"jemanuel","updated_at":"2026-04-26T00:04:49.396399Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["architecture","audit","modes-of-reasoning","wezterm"]}
